The ANC in the Western Cape has described the death of fellow comrade Patrick Jelele as deeply saddening. Jelele who succumbed to COVID-19 was the first chairperson of the branch in Ward 93, Khayelitsha. He was also the husband of African National Congress (ANC) Women’s League Provincial Coordinator, Lulama Jelele. Jelele died at the Khayelitsha Day Hospital after battling the disease. He is survived by his wife and four daughters. Over 40 new COVID-19 related deaths South Africa’s COVID-19 death toll has now risen to 1 674, an increase of 49. The Western Cape, which is the epicentre of the virus in the country, accounts for 46 of these deaths, while the other three are from the Eastern Cape. The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases is 80 412  and the total number of recoveries to date is 44 331. This translates to a recovery rate of 55.1%. The Infographic below provides a provincial breakdown of cases:  Free State  North West  Gauteng  Mpumalanga  Northern Cape Eastern Cape  Limpopo  KwaZulu-Natal Western Cape COVID-19 STATISTICS IN SOUTH AFRICA sabcnews.com |  SABC News channel | SABC Radio news SOURCE: Department of Health  & ﻿National Institute of Communicable Diseases  CASES GAUTENG WESTERN CAPE KWAZULU-NATAL EASTERN CAPE FREE STATE LIMPOPO NORTH WEST MPUMALANGA NORTHERN CAPE 4238 608 416 1402 391 211 UNALLOCATED 52 AS AT 17 June 2020 251 DEATHS 9 1 243 87 73 5 CONFIRMED CASES | 80 412 DEATHS | 1674 TESTS CONDUCTED | 1 200 736 RECOVERIES | 44 331 NEW CASES | 4 078 46 ﻿555 14 ﻿620 11 ﻿919 1 4 1 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document));